\begin_layout Section

\lang english
Data Governance and Classification Policy
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "pol:1.11"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Policy Metadata

\lang english
Effective:
 July 01,
 2026
\begin_inset space \hfill{}
\end_inset

Version:
 1.0
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy establishes a mandatory governance framework for identifying,
 classifying,
 and protecting Elko County data assets.
 The County shall assign value and sensitivity to information so security controls are applied consistently and proportionally to the risk of unauthorized access,
 disclosure,
 modification,
 destruction,
 or loss of availability.
 This policy mandates data stewardship and security attribute association while preserving statutory transparency obligations under Nevada law.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all data created,
 received,
 maintained,
 processed,
 stored,
 or transmitted by Elko County,
 regardless of format (digital,
 physical,
 or audiovisual) or location (on-premises,
 cloud-hosted,
 mobile,
 or third-party managed).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This includes,
 but is not limited to:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Production Data
\series default
:
 Records,
 databases,
 and application files supporting County operations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Operational and Security Data
\series default
:
 System logs,
 audit trails,
 configuration data,
 and network telemetry.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Physical Media
\series default
:
 Printed documents,
 tapes,
 portable media,
 and removable storage devices.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
All data residing on County infrastructure or processed on behalf of the County is County property.
 The use of unsanctioned systems,
 repositories,
 or "Shadow IT" to store or process County data is prohibited.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Board of County Commissioners
\series default
:
 Upon adoption of this policy,
 the Board delegates authority to the IT Director to administer retention and disposition procedures for Information Operations records and IT-managed data assets in accordance with Nevada retention schedules,
 County directives,
 and applicable legal holds.
 This delegation applies to Information Operations records and IT-managed data assets and shall not be interpreted as superseding statutory duties assigned to other County offices.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director
\series default
:
 Shall serve as the primary governance authority for data classification and data security.
 The IT Director shall:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Define and enforce the County Data Classification Schema and mandatory safeguards.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Serve as the 
\series bold
Local Agency Security Officer (LASO)
\series default
 and provide direct oversight for Criminal Justice Information (CJI) within County-controlled systems.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Serve as the 
\series bold
Information Operations Records Custodian
\series default
 under Board delegation for Information Operations records and IT-managed data assets,
 including retention and disposition procedures.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Ensure required technical controls,
 handling standards,
 and exception decisions are implemented and enforced County-wide for County-managed systems.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Terminal Agency Coordinator (TAC)
\series default
:
 Shall serve as the operational CJIS program point of contact for the County.
 The TAC shall coordinate CJIS operational requirements (including user administration processes,
 CJIS audit support,
 and CJIS compliance communications) with the LASO,
 CSA/CSO as applicable,
 and County stakeholders.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Department Heads (Data Owners)
\series default
:
 Shall classify departmental data at creation or intake,
 ensure access is limited to authorized personnel based on business need-to-know,
 and ensure departmental processes comply with the handling requirements defined in this policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Information Operations Personnel (Data Custodians)
\series default
:
 Shall implement and operate the technical controls (e.g.,
 access enforcement,
 encryption,
 segmentation,
 logging) required to protect data according to its assigned classification.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
All County Personnel
\series default
:
 Shall handle,
 transmit,
 and store data in accordance with this policy and the assigned classification.
 Personnel shall report suspected misclassification,
 mishandling,
 or unauthorized disclosure promptly through established reporting channels to the IT Director.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
4.
 Compliance and Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Adherence to this policy is mandatory for all County departments and personnel.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Mandatory Classification
\series default
:
 All County data shall be classified.
 Data not yet classified shall be handled as Restricted until formally evaluated and assigned a classification level.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Public Records and Legal Precedence
\series default
:
 Security classification shall not be treated as an automatic exemption from disclosure.
 Public records requests under NRS 239 shall be handled through the County’s established legal review process.
 When classification controls appear to conflict with a public records obligation,
 the District Attorney’s Office shall provide binding guidance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Conflict Hierarchy
\series default
:
 In any conflict,
 statutory requirements (NRS) and CJIS Security Policy requirements shall take precedence,
 followed by County policy,
 then departmental procedures.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Records Retention
\series default
:
 Retention periods shall be applied in accordance with the Nevada Local Government Records Retention Schedule and County retention requirements.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
IT security logs,
 including access control and audit logs,
 shall be retained for a minimum of three (3) calendar years from the end of the calendar year in which the review or audit was concluded,
 per the applicable Nevada Local Government Records Retention Schedule for IT Security Audit Records (currently LRDA 20071728).
 This exceeds the CJIS minimum of one (1) year.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
For CJIS audit records,
 the greater of the CJIS minimum (one year) or the applicable Nevada retention requirement shall apply.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Director shall ensure Information Operations retention and disposition actions are suspended during litigation holds,
 public records preservation requirements,
 audits,
 or other legal hold events.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Enforcement and Sanctions
\series default
:
 Unauthorized disclosure or mishandling of Confidential or Restricted information may result in corrective action,
 disciplinary action up to and including termination,
 referral for investigation,
 and/or criminal prosecution under applicable law (including NRS 205).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exceptions
\series default
:
 Exceptions to this policy shall be documented with justification and approved by the IT Director in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.04"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 and 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Any exception involving Restricted CJI shall require explicit written approval of the IT Director (as LASO) and,
 where applicable,
 written approval by the CSA/CSO or other CJIS governing authority required by governing agreements.
 All such approvals shall be retained for audit.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
